The paper discusses the application of machine learning and data mining algorithms in bioinformatics, which falls under the category of computational biology and bioinformatics. The paper specifically focuses on scalable computing and storage designs, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of Large Scale Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper mentions classification, clustering, regression, graphical model-based learning, and dimensionality reduction, which are all common topics in machine learning and data mining research. Therefore, it is likely that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of Quantitative Methods (q-bio.QM) or Genomics (q-bio.GN), as well as Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) due to the engineering maxim mentioned in the abstract.
